reviews.review_text: Help>Slipknot>Franklins 10-11-77 bid a fine farewell to the always excellent triumvirate of Help/Slipknot/Franklin's, at least until the groove returned in the 80s. Definitely my favorite versions of all three songs.  Just listen that bass drum to start the show.  You know its going to be a winner. A super funky show that brings the dance machine straight to your brain and doesnt let up.  Lesh slides all over the fretless, Jerry wails, and the second set throws down bigtime.  Perhaps the show that converted me to the Dead after Pigpen.  Enjoy.

Great show This is a really good show, the bouncy dancing groove (the Dead's take on disco?) really dominates, but doesn't distract from a great show. The sound is almost 100%, a few glitches in NFA are really minor points, it is a real good SBD recording! Download and enjoy!
In top 10 of my 100hrs so far This show SMOKES! And so should you! 5 stars, What are you waiting for?

Not fade From the deal>let it grow (which is one of the best I have heard to the hot dancin estimated>eyes which is another for the record books, great show all the way around even for '77.

PS this is most definately one of the funkiest and most ripping estimateds and the NOT FADE ++ they are on steroids just cannot get enough of this....
I don't get it.... I don't know what Dick or any of you see in this show, it really isn't that good. Jerry is OFF. Cool dancin' and NFA but thats about it.

Moments... This show definitely has its moments (Let It Grow, Dancin', NFA), but overall, there are much better 77 shows out there.  Powerful Deal ending is of honorable mention.  Great sound quality, but I tend to agree with 4x4, Jerry is off overall.  However, the rest of the band is on for the most part.  I'd give it a 3.5, but I cant so...4.
Maybe not a 1977 top 10, but a damn fine help->slip->frank (and then it was bon voyage) and an epic let it grow.  Worth a listen and a selective download.

Jerry off?  Not by a long shot this rips The two people that said that have reviewed a combined 6 shows. I have listened to over 300 on LMA and this let it grow is one of the best on the whole site as is the est>eyes and very hot not fade to boot. 

I cringe whenever I see one guy sid weiss come in and give a show 12 people have given a 5 and he gives it a 2 or 3 because he says it has 'bad sound' no he is just a twisted fruit with an anti social bent. If you cannot honestly and intelligently rate this go back to XLII's.

My advice going forward get guidance from the folks who have consistently proven their credibility in picking kind shows like this. Enough said...

I agree!!!!!!!!!!! I most defiantly agree with the last two reviewers. This show is a ripper!!!!!!!!! Help>Slip>Frank is sick, the Let It Grow is one of the best I have heard too and this Dancin' is also one of my favorites. The audio quality is very good and itÃÂs from one of the best taping years. What are you waiting for download this one now!!!!!!!!!!!! You will not be sorry.

Tasty Performance The show starts out on a booming note with Phil smoking through an outstanding Help On The Way, which unfortunately is abruptly cut in this file.  The show features an exquisite rendition of Peggy O.  Jerry's finger work in this number builds gradually to a nice crescendo.  The highlight of this show is the funkalicious Dancin' In The Streets JAM (17Min)!  The recording quality is outstanding.    This is a must have for the serious.

Oh Peggy O!!!!!!!!!! This was the first boot I ever heard, Thank You Brian C. KHS class of 92', I used to sit in my basement with headphones and listen to this tape and when I heard Jerrry sing Peggy-O my perspective on what music could do changed forever, God Bless the Grateful Dead....

Picture Perfect Flaws This show is crazy good!!! People would look at this show with all the patches and flaws and bypass it, I almost did, but I'll tell you what, download this show and you won't regret it, The beginning of this show HOTW >SLP >FRNK starts off a lil' sloppy but tightens up, Jack Straw is sick, Peggy-O and Let it Grow are fantastic, Dancin', Estimated and Eyes are also sick, this Eyes is my second fav., next to 9/11/74. If anyone has or knows of a better Eyes than 9/11/74 please let me know. Now getting back to those flaws or patches whatever you want to call them sick placements for all. and thank you for the good work, on this show

my first This was the first GD show I ever heard, little more than a year ago, and I haven't looked back since.  From Phil's perfect drop into Franklin's Tower, I knew I'd been missing some serious masterpieces all my life. This is one of my favorite H>S!>F jams.  Jerry rips it up on Let it Grow and Dancin' is super funky, also one of the best of the year.  
The Estimated>Eyes jam is really good, as is the Not Fade Away.
Definitely check this show out, got me hooked.

Lock bolt and key I don't know, this H>S>F is alright, kind of short Slipknot. I think better versions lie in earlier '77. Personally I think even 6/14/91 is a better version (of Slipknot particularly). I would rate this show more for the Let it Grow, Dancin and solid versions of everything in the 2nd set. 
In my opinion, 10/29 is a better show from this month.

A 1977 GEM! Anyone who gave this show less than 4 stars is either retarded, tone-deaf or a complete snob.

This very well may be my favorite show...I'm addicted to the Dancin' and NFA 

H>S>F, Jack Straw, Let it Grow, Dancin', Dire Wolf, NFA and Around just might be the best versions ever.

BTW If you love the NFA in this show (you should if you're normal) then check out the NFA on 10/15/77

Latvala was right on with this show, so are you downloading yet?

stormin' in norman... sorry for the cheesy pun, but.... it's fucking true, jizz... these cats are just smoking on this night. help/slip/frank is always great to hear, but it's jack straw that really starts to bring the hammer down. peggy-o is sparse and gorgeous, deal is boss as always from this yr, and this version of let it grow is one of my faves from this era, crushing and delicate at the same time. the second set is really where this scene starts to get wild. the sequence from estimated thru wharf rat is the grateful goddamn dead at their finest, with a near perfect eyes, and a mind-colonic of a not fade away. this show'll fix you right up, if indeed you need fixing. if you don't, well, just let it kick your ass.

God Bless You, Mr Latvala!!! This is the show!!!!  This show is the show that is hidden in pieces on Dicks Picks #29!!!
 = Set 2 Pt.1 and Pt.3 = 

*One slight downer about this show... 
....H>S>F, definitely ends to fast.

Comments on comments, sorry While this show may not be the best 1977 has to offer, I'll say it's definitely a keeper.  Killer sdbd, great setlist and overall a great performance.

OK, now my rant which is general in nature.....who the fuck cares if 4.5 seconds of a song is cut, don't download it then.  The AUD patch of 6 seconds on Good Lovin' is horrible, don't download it then.  The version of Eyes on 9-11-74 is much better than this version, don't download it then.  John Doe has only written 3 reviews and doesn't know what he's talkin about, don't download it then.  Jerry is way off for 8 seconds on Wharf Rat and he screws up 7 words of lyrics. don't download it then.  I think you get my point.  ALL THIS MUSIC IS FREE, SO WHY BITCH?!

Archives has broken new ground for downloading and we should all be thankful.

Relatively mediocre The sound quality of this recording is typical of 77 boards, which is to say it's good.  But the performance is lacking - and this is coming from a 77 fanatic. I agree with the other reviewers who feel that Jerry is off.  He muffs a number of lyrics and his playing is generally uninspired relative to other shows from this era.  While there are a few highlights, overall this show is for completists only.
-------
Man, I come back and check in on this a year later and find several people spewing negativity on those of us who don't love this show.  I don't get it.  If we're all supposed to have the same opinion what's the point of posting comments?  The idea is to provide some opinions to help folks make informed decisions as to which shows they might like to DL.  I read these comments all the time and I find them extremely helpful in filtering shows.  May I respectfully suggest: time for a head check folks.  What are you hoping to accomplish by bashing other reviewers?  And yeah, I broke the "comments pertaining to the show rule" too now.  I apologize, but my goat was got.  For penance I will now blaze a sacrificial bowl and listen to 3 Scarlet->Fires.  Peace.

Nice 77' 77 was just a monster year period. october 77 is probably second only to may of 77 as the best month, and this may be one of the top shows of october...the H>S>F is one of the most mellowest combo of these songs, and it is a good one, but a little short...it still packs a good punch....
the rest of the show takes off after dancin, which is a grove fest....dire wolf is a strong one coming off the high of dancin and well the show is just a good solid 77 show...

somewhere in between In typical Dead fashion the first set is quite sloppy, but we do get a taste of classic GD in the second set.  I will mention that overall, the sound quality is pretty darn good.  Help Slip Frank is besieged by foibles on Jerry's part.  Let It Grow has some hard edged jams and an improvised rock progression thrown into the jam.  Dancin' gets us definitely on the right track.  After a slow down Dire Wolf, Estimated through Around and Around comprises a seamless jam and the band is energetic and powerful.  This is not a perfect show, nor does it rival the best shows of '77, however the second set jam is worth at least a listen...

Birthday Boy This show may have it's issues, but I have to love it. I was born while this show was happening. Shot out of the womb like Phil's opening bass line on Help. 700 miles away, but I knew what was happening.

Instrument balance great. Watch out for the Slip cut, it will take you by surprise.

Noble Center LET IT GROW LET IT GROW LET IT GROW LET IT GROW

LIG is fierce and worth the download alone.

H/S/F starts off the show sloppy, but they do come around.

fun stuff No it aint perfect, but is anything after 6/9/77?( or before!) maybe, it all hides subtle ideas for us to run with. Sometimes a small portion, a song, even an split second inside 3 hours of playing drives you  and is worth the experience, Phils bass line in the second Roll Away the Dew in the First Corus of Franklin's Tower does that for me, a little John Kahn influenced maybe.  Also Keith's post spring77 style of playing is special in its own right, 
  five stars for unique qualities, not worth missing.
I admit I could be more critical, and realize I tend to only review my 5star shows, after all, they are the ones worth getting excited about.

hear this A few misses, but plenty of highlights to keep everyone grinning.  Can't go wrong with a nice (if a bit short) Help/Slip/Franklin to start the show.  Jack Straw is very strong, and Let it Grow is a first set stunner. Jerry gets super fat 'n funky in Dancin to start the second, with Eyes and NFA the highlights of a quality set.  No letdown throughout... good sound... don't overlook this show.

Grateful for nugets.net I just downloaded the SBD from site above. It sounds very good - maybe a tiny bit lower quality than some other 77s, but not much.  The EYES is so damn good - it just grooves along effortlessly.

Sound check The Candyman sound check was arguably as good as anything they played later that night. I've been listening to the tape of this performance since the night of the show and have never tired of it.

why so many complaints ? speaking for myself only i feel really self-centered and un-grateful for even complaining about sound quality... jerry forgetting a few words wawawawaw also i,m glad we have a site such as this where all this free music is available for us to critique. internet archive your doing a swell job keep it up

5-1/2 years and 400 shows until Help>Slip!>Franklin's reappears 101177: The last Help>Slip>Franklin's w/Donna & Keith; gotta love how Jerry ad-libs on the lyrics, "It rings like fire if you lose you way.....Yes,it will!" Phil..is, well, 1977 Phil. There is "something" about this show that is special in its own imperfect perfection.

It was mentioned earlier: selections from this show can be found as "hidden tracks" on Dick's Picks #29 (Disc 2: "NFA>Wharf Rat?>Around..." Disc #5: "Dancin'>Dire Wolf") 

A heartfelt "Thank You" to all of the individuals who have done all the work to keep the music alive --- AshesRising
lord the day i cant hear these shows, is the day i throw in the fuckin towel. cuz this life is a mutha.

LIG 110% agree with flashbackmagic on the Let if Grow.  Everyone's 'on'.  Jer's firing off aggressive licks during the V and C and some firey jamming.  Effing amazing - only could have possible been better with some Weather Reports before it.

Overall a 4 star show IMO.
Road Trips This Help>Slip>Franklin was just released on the Road Trips series. This Let it Grow melts face. Turn it up!
WHY? WHY CAN I NOT GET THE LAST COUPLE OF SONGS?

Good show Let it Grow is amped and love the Lazy Lightning tease in the jam.

Recording is ok.

Don't know any mess about which these others speak, just enjoyin what they give me instead of cryin about what they don't. Jerry's dead, so I don't know what he woulda done except that I do know he drove around in a BMW. Thus, I suspect he loved money too. If you didn't know him, can you honestly speak on what he woulda done? After all, no one thought he'd take back to doing what killed him.

boo hoo Please grade the shows!  This one is especially sweet!  5 stars 4 sure!  slipknot is sick as sick gets!  Maybe I'm drunk, but there are plenty of sites to get the old vault material for free....yeah, it is bogus that money drives the world, but such is America!  and americans.
The dead was and still is a huge positive influence in lifes all over the world....cherish what is given to you....it is doubtful that I would have gone to this show, unless I saw the "road tripz" posting in dead.net.....don't buy it, just listen here.....be well heads, don't be bitter.

SHUT THE F//K UP AND STOP BITCHIN' FIRST OFF OF ALL THE TIMES I HAVE LISTENED TO THIS SHOW I STILL CANNOT FIND ONE NOTE THAT IS WEAK. START TO END IT IS MORE OR LESS PERFECT.YO ''KIMOCK FIEND'' YOU ARE ONE ANGRY DUDE MAN.WHY IS IT THAT YOU AND MANY PEOPLE LIKE YOU HAVE A PROBLEM WITH ROAD TRIPS?  SO WHAT THEY ARE NOT COMPLETE SHOWS. HOW ABOUT YOU TRY THIS PUT THE DISC IN YOUR PLAYER HIT PLAY AND JUST SIT BACK AND DIG WHAT IS THERE.MAYBE YOU JUST DO NOT GET ''IT''.WHAT IS THIS SHIT ABOUT BRENT'S DEATH PUSHED JERRY BACK TO DOING DOPE? OBVIOUSLY YOU DON'T KNOW THIS BUT BRENT AND JERRY KEPT CLOSE ON THE ROAD BECAUSE THEY WERE DOING THE SAME THING AND COPPED FROM THE SAME DUDE.YOU ALSO TRASH WEIR ABOUT SELLING THE VAULT AND I ALSO DON'T THINK THE MUSIC SHOULD BE SOLD BUT YOUR ''IDOL'' BILL GRAHAM WAS ONE OF THE GREEDIEST DUDES AROUND BEFORE HE DIED.AT WINTERLAND BILL WOULD GET FULL TICKETS FROM PEOPLE AFTER THEY ENTERED THE SHOW AND SELL THEM AGAIN IN THE PARKING LOT[I GOT THEM MORE THAN A FEW TIMES THANKZ BILL].YOU NEED TO UP YOUR DOSE OF PROZAC.
10-11-77 Just wanted to let my fellow deadheads know you can download this show for free at nugs.net stash. I downloaded it yesterday and it is a good recording of a real nice show.

Rhino shit can't beleive that even an aud recording has been taken due the Rhino release of road trips.

MORE BONER POWDER !

Wow! Review for show--obviously not for recording, since it isn't accessible :-(  Everyone's tastes are different and the range of other reviews is enlightening. But to this 1977 fanatic, this show is up there with Boston, Cornell, Buffalo, the Fox (19th), the Mosque, and May 1 at the Palladium. No matter how great those shows, they all have at least a couple songs where the gang is simply going through the motions (eg, almost the entire first set of Cornell). There isn't a single song this night that doesn't have something very special about it.

...___[:]o

Latvala said it - this night is primal GD energy! I love this H>S>F and it's definitely in top 5 of the year no doubt about that. My favorite of '77 has to be 6/9 Winterland. Anyways I think this Dancin' is 2nd best to 5/8. Nothing can beat that one as far as the Disco Dead versions, but this one is nearly as good. Overall a great show but def. listen to this Dancin' in the Streets if u like the disco version

Classic second set Everyone talks about the Help>Slip>Franklin's, and perhaps deservedly so (though I have others I prefer) but it's the second set jams that have really drawn me into this one. Everything from Dancin' on is great, and this set carries a unique, almost minimalist, hypnotic funk quality that really grows on you. My favorite part of the set is the part of the show that was never officially released: Estimated>Eyes is one of the best parings of those tunes of the year, with the Estimated being particularly groovy.

Front row for my first Dead show Thanks to my brother Drew for staying out all night and getting front row tickets to this show. I knew from the opening that this was going to be a special show. During slip knot the whole bands watching Jerry as he shakes his head no then when he finally says yes and they hit the final progression to go into Franklins Tower I seriously melted!! This show was awesome in spite of the crowd that would not get up and dance. Being my first show I was unaware that you get up and dance at a Dead concert. So glad to be able to hear this show again.
Paradise waits... ;)

Jerry's voice is quite beautiful here Slow and deliberate with all the soul and warmth. Loved all of this one. LIG is special. Second set is gorgeous, Eyes is a slow ride home on the surrey with fringe on top. Wharf Rat too.
Lots of booming bass here.

Amazing NFA How come no mentioned the amazing NFA kam, Jerry and Keith playing off each other, everyone taking turns...
Another amazing and different 77 show....
So Good! Wow. That "LIG", that "Dancin'"...they sound fantastic here. Fun stuff, dig in!
